snippet: Ms. Babs was already an established pop singer in Sweden when she drew praise for her appearances on Duke Ellington’s “Sacred Concerts.”
abstract: Alice Babs, a Swedish singer acclaimed for her work with Duke Ellington, dies at age 90.
lead_paragraph: Ms. Babs was already an established pop singer in Sweden when she drew praise for her appearances on Duke Ellington’s “Sacred Concerts.”

headline.main: Alice Babs, Who Sang for Ellington, Dies at 90
headline.print_headline: Alice Babs, 90, a Singer for Duke Ellington
